TIP TOP GAL took back off of the fast early pace, saved ground to the quarter marker, tipped three wide for the drive, made a steady bid in the lane but lacked the needed late response. LAGATHA hustled leaving the break and dueled with LOTSA PEPPER through quick early fractions, could not keep pace with that rival nearing the top of the stretch and tired in the drive. KNOCKOUT BERT lunged at the start and spotted the field in the early stages, rallied four deep nearing the quarter marker, battled for the lead in mid-stretch, took command nearing the sixteenth-marker, was all out in deep stretch and was tagged in the final strides for the win, while holding for place. RHODIUM RUNNER showed early speed, pressed the pace between horses to the turn, dueled with ZERO BUCKS GIVEN to the quarter marker while carving moderate fractions, battled with KNOCKOUT BERT to mid-stretch, could not keep pace in the late stages and held safely for show. ZERO BUCKS GIVEN broke alertly and contested the early pace while inside of rivals, dueled with RHODIUM RUNNER while carving moderate fractions through the turn, battled to mid-stretch and gave way in the final furlong. GREGS CITY ZIP bumped with THAT'S BIND BABE at the start, recovered and contested the early pace while outside of rivals, pressed the pace to the quarter marker and faded in the drive.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: REV REE threw her head at the break and was off a step slowly, was allowed to settle in the early stages, advanced on the far turn, mounted a four wide rally into the drive, closed well nearing the furlong marker, raced on the left lead while battling to the sixteenth-marker and made a late surge in the final strides to prevail. SHEZAGHOST broke alertly and dictated terms into the first turn, set decent fractions through the backstretch run, was confronted by GHOSTLY GAL nearing the quarter marker, battled with that rival to mid-stretch, engaged with REV REE in deep stretch and was gamely bested in the final strides, while just holding for second. GHOSTLY GAL forwardly placed in the early stages, stalked the decent fractions to the half-mile marker, confronted SHEZAGHOST nearing the quarter pole, battled with that rival to the furlong pole, felt pressure late from REV REE and grudgingly gave way in the final strides, while just missing for place and holding safely for show. CLOCKSTRIKESTWELVE unhurried in the early going, trailed to the quarter marker, roused in upper stretch, angled out inside of the furlong pole, closed willingly in the final sixteenth but could not impact the leaders in the end. UNDISTURBED settled off of the early pace, was well positioned through the backstretch run, came within range along the second turn and did not offer a late rally in the drive. LA VIKINA promient into the first turn, tracked the decent pace from an inside path through the backstretch run, lost ground on the second turn, ran evenly to mid-stretch and weakened in the late stages. MADEIRA WINE a bit slow into stride early on, was keen along the first turn and pulled to be close to the pace entering the backstretch run, settled and advanced while three wide on the far turn, could not keep pace leaving the quarter marker and tired in the stretch run.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: GOLDEN GATE FIELDS RACE 8 1 1/16M All Weather Track CR: 89. Claiming Purse 16000. FOR FOUR YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NOT WON A RACE SINCE OCTOBER 15 OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON FOUR RACES. Weight, 123 lbs. Claiming Price $8,000, if for $7,000, allowed 2 lbs. (Claiming And Starter Races For $6,250 Or Less Not Considered In Eligibility ).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: BIG CITY BANE raced mid-pack under a light hold to the far turn, had to steady a bit near the seven-sixteenths pole and fell back to last, circled the field from there emerging in the stretch six wide, launched a furious rally to get up in time. WALKING BOSS broke in and brushed with ECOLOGIST leaving the start, lagged behind the field, made a bold move on the turn four wide from the three-eighths pole, hit the top of the stretch racing on the wrong lead, quickly straightened out and continued to rally down the stretch, got the best of BRONZE WARRIOR within sight of the finish line but was tagged in the last jump. BRONZE WARRIOR broke well and easily made first run into the clubhouse turn, made the running setting comfortable fractions, still had something left turning for home and finished well, getting outrun in the last sixteenth. DEALERS HAND broke in and brushed with ECOLOGIST, spotting the field a head start, lacked early speed early on and stayed towards the inside, moved closer approaching the far turn, lacked room through the turn, swung four wide into the stretch and finished with some interest but was outfinished in the late stages. SYNC gained the rail while settling behind the early leaders, moved closer down the backstretch, loomed a threat as the field turned for the stretch run and finished evenly but could not find another gear when needed. ECOLOGIST tracked well behind the early leaders through the early stages, was asked to pick up the pace with three furlongs to run, steadied hard when WALKING BOSS crowded him just past the quarter pole and was unable to recover. JEDI KNIGHT hustled from the gate, stalked the pace setting BRONZE WARRIOR to the far turn, moved to challenge approaching the quarter pole but hand nothing left for the stretch run and tired.
